sect1:
Installing Autoconf-&autoconf-version;



The Autoconf package contains programs for producing shell scripts that
can automatically configure source code.

&buildtime; &autoconf-time;
&diskspace; &autoconf-compsize;

&aa-autoconf-down;
&aa-autoconf-dep;

 
 

Installation of Autoconf


Prepare Autoconf for compilation:

./configure --prefix=/usr


Compile the package:

make


To have the results tested, issue:
make check.This takes a long time, about 2 SBUs,
and is strictly optional.


And install the package:

make install



&aa-autoconf-shortdesc;
&aa-autoconf-desc;
